# Implementation Plan - Redesign Doctor Portal UI & Appointment Workflow

This plan outlines the restructuring of the Doctor Portal sidebar navigation, dashboard queue, patient directory history views, and the appointment requests verification workflow.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Proposed Clinic Details Location**:
> We suggest **NOT** showing the large full clinics table directly on the daily patient appointments queue dashboard to keep the dashboard focused. Instead:
> 1. We will place a high-level, compact **Practice Locations Card** at the top or bottom of the dashboard summarizing active clinics and their active status.
> 2. The full management table (adding clinics, editing details, assigning admins) remains in the dedicated **My Clinics** sidebar section, which is cleaner and less distracting.

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Database & Backend API Extensions

We already added the `Comment`, `Report`, and `RejectionReason` columns to the database `Appointments` table and exposed the endpoints. 
We will confirm we have these endpoints working:
- `POST /api/appointments/approve/{id}`: Approves a request (status `Confirmed`), updates optional comment.
- `POST /api/appointments/reject/{id}`: Rejects a request (status `Cancelled`), updates mandatory rejection reason.
- `POST /api/appointments/complete/{id}`: Marks appointment as `Completed`, saves comment and clinical report.
- `POST /api/appointments/move-pending/{id}`: Marks appointment as `Pending` (no-show), saves comment/reason.

